Pre-Game Insights: Baltimore Orioles aim to stop their three-game slide when they face the San Francisco Giants.
San Francisco Giants have a 33-41 record on the road and 74-78 overall.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Orioles have a 42-35 record in home games and the eighth-ranked ERA in the AL.
The Giants have a 33-60 record in games where they've given up a home run.
Others: Thursday's game is the third meeting between the two teams this season.
The Orioles have key players on the injured list, including Ramon Urias and Ryan Mountcastle.
